# Essential Pipeline Scripts Only

Script layout:

- **`scripts/`** (repo root) — **Gitignored.** Agents store temporary scripts here for task automations. Do not commit.
- **`frontend/scripts/`** — Essential frontend pipeline scripts (CI, Lefthook, workflows). Committed.
- **`backend/scripts/`** — Essential backend pipeline scripts (CI, Lefthook, OpenAPI, workflows). Committed.

## Essential Scripts (do not remove)

| Script | Used by | Purpose |
|--------|---------|---------|
| `backend/scripts/check_no_secret_files.sh` | Lefthook (no-secret-files) | Fail commit if `.env` / `.env.local` (or other secret env files) are staged |
| `backend/scripts/run_ruff.sh` | Lefthook (ruff-format, ruff-lint, ruff-backend) | Run Ruff from backend venv (Windows/Unix path handling) |
| `backend/scripts/generate_openapi.py` | Project rules, docs | Regenerate `docs/openapi.json` when API endpoints change |

## Guidelines

- **Agent temp scripts**: Place in root `scripts/` (gitignored). Delete manual-testing scripts after execution; other automations may persist there.
- **Pipeline scripts**: Add to `frontend/scripts/` or `backend/scripts/` only when required by `lefthook.yml`, CI (`.github/workflows/`), or project rules.
- **One-off or personal helpers**: Use root `scripts/` (gitignored) or keep locally; do not add to `frontend/scripts/` or `backend/scripts/`.

## Examples

```markdown
<!-- ❌ BAD - Pipeline script in gitignored root -->
Added scripts/run_ruff.sh (root scripts/ is gitignored; pipeline scripts belong in backend/scripts/).
```

```markdown
<!-- ✅ GOOD - Agent temp script in root (gitignored) -->
Created scripts/one-off-migration.py for task; deleted after run.
```

## Checklist

1. Adding a pipeline script? → Put in `frontend/scripts/` or `backend/scripts/`; confirm it is called by Lefthook, CI, or a project rule.
2. One-off or temp script? → Use root `scripts/` (gitignored); delete if manual-testing per manual-testing-scripts-cleanup rule.
3. Script no longer used by pipeline? → Remove from `frontend/scripts/` or `backend/scripts/`.
